EN: These protests are seen as an outbreak of public discontent.

ZH: 当他们获得自由时，他们的才华脱缰而出。
EN: When they gained their freedom, their talents ran wild.

ZH: 受压抑的情绪终于脱缰了，她失控地嚎啕大哭。
EN: The suppressed emotions finally broke loose and she burst into uncontrollable sobbing.
